1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category as the paper discusses the use of computer vision techniques for automated identification of herbarium specimens. 
2. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper mentions the labeling and identification of specimens, which could involve information retrieval techniques. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible sub-category as the paper mentions the use of deep learning for automated identification. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possibility as the paper may involve natural language processing techniques for labeling and identifying specimens. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possibility as the dataset comprises images of herbarium sheets.
